                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_cyrv" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cyrv</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>cirwæ</orth><form type="variant"><orth>ciwræ</orth></form></form><sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>осадки пива</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>beer sediments</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пивные дрожжи</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>brewers' yeast</q></abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>гуща</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>pulp</q></abv:tr></sense></sense><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example><quote>k˳yvdæn ma jæ fælxortæ ærbajjæfton, bægænyjæn jæ cyrvy byntæ</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>от пиршества я застал только объедки, от пива — осадки</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>I found only leftovers from a feast, from beer — sediments</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III 213</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Вс. %sМиллер%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 151</biblScope></bibl>) сближает с <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>tīvra-</w> <gloss><q>острый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>горчица</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/> <w>trīw</w> <gloss><q>кислый</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>83</biblScope></bibl>). Случайно ли, однако, созвучие с <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>čupra</w> <gloss><q>гуща</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>чапра</w></mentioned>)? Совершенно не убедительно сближение с <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>τιφος</w> <gloss><q>болото</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Petersson</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_LUÅ"/><biblScope>XVI %i3%i 69</biblScope></bibl>).</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Ws. %sMiller%s (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>III 151</biblScope></bibl>) assimilates the word with <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>tīvra-</w> <gloss><q>spicy</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>mustard</q></gloss></mentioned>. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/> <w>trīw</w> <gloss><q>sour</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>83</biblScope></bibl>). Is the assonance with <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>čupra</w> <gloss><q>grounds</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>чапра</w></mentioned>) accidental? Assimilating the word with <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>τῖφος</w> <gloss><q>swamp</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Petersson</author><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_LUÅ"/><biblScope>XVI %i3%i 69</biblScope></bibl>) is completely unconvincing.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>